---
import { SITE } from "@/config";
import { SOCIALS } from "@/constants";
import Socials from "@/components/Socials.astro";
---

<section id="hero" class:list={["pt-8 pb-6", "border-b border-border"]}>
  <h1 class="my-4 text-3xl font-bold sm:my-8 sm:text-4xl">Chaitanya Kulkarni</h1>
  <p class="text-lg font-medium text-accent">AI Engineer</p>
  <p class="mt-4">
    Hello! I'm Chaitanya, a Software and AI Engineer who builds at the intersection of agentic reasoning and high-performance compute.
  </p>
  <p class="mt-3">
    I've spent the last few years turning complex data into autonomous systems. Previously, at Qlik, I architected Agentic AI systems and multimodal RAG pipelines, moving beyond simple chatbots to create "planner-executor" agents that can actually reason through enterprise tasks. This followed my time at Fluke, where I focused on the predictive side of the house — building time-series forecasting systems that solved tangible, high-stakes operational problems.
  </p>
  <p class="mt-3">
    Right now, I'm moving "down the stack" to the engine room. I'm currently deep-diving into LLM inference architectures and GPU optimization, teaching myself the intricacies of CUDA and memory management. By building projects like NanoServe, I'm exploring how to bridge the gap between high-level agentic logic and the low-level compute that makes it possible. I love the challenge of not just making AI smarter, but making it faster and more efficient.
  </p>
  <p class="mt-3">
    Beyond the code, I'm a Master's graduate in Computer Science with a bias toward building production-ready tools. I believe the best AI systems aren't just clever models — they are robust, well-engineered pieces of software that solve real human problems.
  </p>
  {
    SOCIALS.length > 0 && (
      <div class="mt-6">
        <Socials />
      </div>
    )
  }
</section>
